## 2. Requirements

### Functional
  FR-01  Recommend items, runes, and skill order based on live enemy comp and items
  FR-02  Accept screenshot input — extract enemy champion/item data via AI vision
  FR-03  Accept free-text questions (e.g. "what do I build vs heavy AP?")
  FR-04  Ingest custom per-champion resources: YouTube, articles, PDFs, plain notes
  FR-05  Custom resources influence AI answers with higher priority than generic meta
  FR-06  Support multiple AI providers: OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, Ollama (local)
  FR-07  Weekly automated meta refresh from u.gg / lolalytics
  FR-08  Resource manager UI: add, view, delete resources per champion
  FR-09  Settings UI: choose AI provider, enter API key securely
  FR-10  System tray icon with "Open Dashboard" and "Quit" options
  FR-11  Portable: all data stored in data/ folder next to the executable

### Non-Functional
  NFR-01  Must not trigger Riot Vanguard anti-cheat
  NFR-02  Modern, dark-mode browser UI (React + shadcn/ui)
  NFR-03  AI API keys never stored in plaintext — keyring or restricted files
  NFR-04  Server binds to 127.0.0.1 only — unreachable from network
  NFR-05  All endpoints authenticated — session token + constant-time comparison
  NFR-06  Replay attack protection on AI calls (30s timestamp window)
  NFR-07  Rate limiting: 10 req/min on /ask, 5 req/min on /resources
  NFR-08  Single portable .exe — no installer, no Python or Node required
  NFR-09  Responds to /ask within 5 seconds on a mid-range PC
  NFR-10  ChromaDB data and settings persist in data/ folder across restarts

