## 4. Data Flow

### 4.1 Live Game Flow (Real-Time)
  1. Riot Poller (asyncio task) GETs /liveclientdata/allgamedata every 5s
  2. Raw payload is sanitised → only activePlayer, allies, enemies, gameTime retained
  3. Validated into GameState Pydantic model (strict, extra=forbid)
  4. GameState broadcast to all connected browser WS clients
  5. React dashboard renders live enemy comp + items automatically

### 4.2 Build Recommendation Flow (/api/ask)
  1. Browser sends POST /api/ask with:
       { question, champion, role, gameState (optional), timestamp }
  2. Middleware validates: session token → rate limit → timestamp window (30s)
  3. RAG retrieval: ChromaDB similarity search on champion namespace
       → top 3-5 chunks from custom resources (e.g. Lathyrus Bard video)
  4. Meta lookup: SQLite query for champion+role win-rate build (latest patch)
  5. Context bundle assembled:
       [Live enemies + items] + [Meta build] + [RAG chunks]
  6. LLM prompt constructed with priority instruction:
       "Prefer user-provided resources over generic meta when they conflict"
  7. AI API call (provider from settings, key from keyring)
  8. Structured response returned: { items[], runes, skillOrder, rationale }

### 4.3 Resource Ingestion Flow (/api/resources POST)
  1. User submits { champion, url, label, type } from Resource Manager UI
  2. URL validated (Pydantic HttpUrl) + champion name sanitised
  3. Dispatcher routes by type:
       YouTube  → youtube-transcript-api fetches transcript
       Article  → httpx GET + BeautifulSoup text extraction
       PDF      → PyMuPDF text extraction
       Note     → raw text stored directly
  4. LangChain RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter (chunk=500, overlap=50)
  5. Chunks embedded via provider's embedding model
  6. Stored in ChromaDB under champion namespace with metadata:
       { source_url, label, champion, ingested_at, chunk_index }
  7. Resource record written to SQLite (id, champion, url, label, type, status)

### 4.4 Screenshot Flow
  1. User pastes/drops screenshot onto dashboard
  2. Browser encodes as base64, sends with POST /api/ask
  3. Vision-capable model (GPT-4o / Gemini 2.0 Flash) extracts:
       enemy champion names, their items, approximate gold
  4. Extracted data merged into GameState and proceeds as 4.2

### 4.5 Meta Refresh Flow (Weekly Cron)
  1. APScheduler triggers every Monday 03:00 local time
  2. httpx GETs champion build pages from u.gg (top win-rate builds per patch)
  3. BeautifulSoup parses: core items, rune page, win rate, pick rate
  4. Riot Data Dragon JSON fetched for latest patch item stats
  5. SQLite meta table upserted — old entries for same champion+role+patch replaced
  6. No external service — entirely local, no API key required

